embeds.title: Help
embeds.description:
If you find yourself using this, chances are you've hit a roadblock! Don't worryâ€”I'm here to assist you!

To begin, if you're tweaking a message, use **ModifyMessage**. This needs both a true or false value and the text value. If either is missing, it won't function! If it's true, it will reset everything with your provided text; if false, it will append your text.

Now, let's talk about **ModifyAttachment**. This only needs the attachment/parameter! If you already have an image, it will replace it with the new one. If there's no image at all, it will add one.

There is also a **DeleteAttachment** option using this will simply delete the attachment!

Introducing **ModifyMessageColor**. Simply provide the hex code as the text value. If there's no existing color, it will assign one for you. Easy as pie!

**RemoveMessageColor** does the same as **DeleteAttachment** just removing the color from the message!

**ApplyTag**: This function adds your search to a specified tag. Please ensure that the tag already exists. Conversely, **RemoveTag** removes a tag from your search. Use the text command parameter to pick a tag!

**DuplicateSearch** will duplicate any search! Insert the search name under title and the new name under text!

**ModifyThumbnail** and **ModifyAttatchment** will only accept tenor or imgur links. These can be gotten by right clicking the image or gif and copying image address!
```
https://i.imgur.com/
```
```
https://c.tenor.com/
```
```
https://media1.tenor.com/m/
```

embeds.title: ModifyMessage -> ModifyMessage
embeds.description:
**ModifyMessage**

The ModifyMessage function is employed to alter the content of a message. The message content is allowed to include anything except three ` You can utilize the TrueOrFalse input to decide whether it should reset the entire message (True) or simply append to it (False).

embeds.title: ModifySearch -> Attachment's
embeds.description:
**Modify Attachment**

The section for modifying attachments manages the addition and editing of an embed object. When adding an image, you must use either Imgur or Tenor GIF. To insert an image or GIF, right-click on it and copy its image address, or on mobile, copy the image address.

**Delete Attachment**

This function removes the attachment from your search.

**How to add image**
Below under the text input add your link inside the text input box!

embeds.title: ModifySearch -> Thumbnail's
embeds.description:
**Modify Thumbnail**

This section is dedicated to editing the thumbnail of your search. Similar to images, thumbnails use the same file system. You need to use either Imgur or Tenor GIF to insert an image or GIF. To add an image or GIF, right-click on it and copy its image address, or on mobile, copy the image address.

**Delete Thumbnail**

This function deletes the thumbnail from your search.

**How to add image**
Below under the text input add your link inside the text input box!

embeds.title: ModifySearch -> Tag's
embeds.description:
**Apply Tag**
This function is employed to assign tags to searches. Utilize the `/find` command to display them. To apply a tag, simply input the title of your desired tag.

**Remove Tag**
This function removes a tag from a search. Input the tag's title in text to complete the removal process.

**How to Add Tag**
Beneath the text input, enter your tag's title.

**NOTE**
If you delete a search, it will still appear in tags. However, there's no need to worry, as the search itself is gone. You can use the `removetag` option to eliminate its tag, even if the search is no longer present.

embeds.title: ModifySearch -> Color's
embeds.description:
**Modify Message Color**
To employ this feature, input your hex code. This enables you to change the color of your messages.

**Remove Message Color**
This function eliminates the color from your messages.

**How to Add Color**
Below the text input, insert your color hex code (Only hex codes are accepted!).

embeds.title: ModifySearch -> Locking Message
embeds.description:
**Lock Search**
This function secures your search, allowing only individuals with the "view lock search" permission to access it.

**Unlock Search**
This function opens up a search for everyone to view.

embeds.title: ModifySearch -> Edit Text
embeds.description:
**Edit Text:**
The edit lock feature functions as a tool for making modifications to a specific segment of text as needed. When set to "True," it will update all occurrences of the edited text. If set to "False," it will only modify the initial instance.

**Example:**

Original message:
```
I love wireframe (early test)

I love wireframe (early test)
```

Replacing "I love" with "I extra love" and "early test" with "early tester":

If set to True:
```
I extra love wireframe (early tester)

I extra love wireframe (early test)
```

If set to False:
```
I extra love wireframe (early tester)

I love wireframe (early test)
```
